00:19:57.450 --> 00:19:59.250
of millions of others would--

00:19:59.250 --> 00:20:05.100
so DNA is not a unique
identifier for true identity.

00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:10.110
So the concepts of
identity for things

00:20:10.110 --> 00:20:12.252
that I think about
sometimes, some of the papers

00:20:12.252 --> 00:20:12.960
were about three.

00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:18.450
But there's attributes, a claim,
a credential, an attestation.

00:20:18.450 --> 00:20:19.920
What would be an attribute?

00:20:19.920 --> 00:20:23.803
Just any old attribute of a--

00:20:23.803 --> 00:20:24.745
anybody?

00:20:27.262 --> 00:20:28.197
AUDIENCE: Your retina.

00:20:28.197 --> 00:20:29.280
GARY GENSLER: Your retina.

00:20:29.280 --> 00:20:34.180
Or it could be your age,
address, citizenship, name.

00:20:34.180 --> 00:20:37.140
A claim is, my name is Gary.

00:20:37.140 --> 00:20:39.900
Or a claim might
be, I am so old.

00:20:39.900 --> 00:20:44.440
Or I am a US citizen.

00:20:44.440 --> 00:20:51.670
Or a claim might even be, I
have $5,000 in my bank account.

00:20:51.670 --> 00:20:53.560
There are other forms of claims.

00:20:53.560 --> 00:20:57.310
Or I do have a bank
account at Bank of America.

00:20:59.830 --> 00:21:02.140
I don't think I have
$5,000 in it right now.

00:21:02.140 --> 00:21:03.790
No.

00:21:03.790 --> 00:21:08.330
A credential is what
we started with.

00:21:08.330 --> 00:21:13.300
I think James mentioned it, a
driver's license, an ID card,

00:21:13.300 --> 00:21:15.730
a utility bill sometimes.

00:21:15.730 --> 00:21:18.640
I mean there's hundreds
of forms of credentials.

00:21:18.640 --> 00:21:23.170
We think of the
governmental credentials.

00:21:23.170 --> 00:21:27.570
The history of credentials
is interesting.

00:21:27.570 --> 00:21:30.730
The first tens of thousands
of years of human kind

00:21:30.730 --> 00:21:33.460
didn't have any.

00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:35.410
And we started to have them.

00:21:35.410 --> 00:21:42.430
Passports really aren't even
that old of an invention.

00:21:42.430 --> 00:21:46.150
In the 16th century, the King of
England had some pass boarding.

00:21:46.150 --> 00:21:48.940
But it was so that
his citizens could be

00:21:48.940 --> 00:21:50.740
recognized in other countries.

00:21:50.740 --> 00:21:52.990
It was so that their
rights would be respected

00:21:52.990 --> 00:21:57.690
and somebody would
not be messed with.

00:21:57.690 --> 00:22:02.510
I'm under that sovereign,
don't mess with me.

00:22:02.510 --> 00:22:05.350
But in terms of a true
permitting system,

00:22:05.350 --> 00:22:08.560
it was largely implemented
about 100 years ago.

00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:10.660
Anywhere between 100
and 150 years ago.

00:22:10.660 --> 00:22:12.910
It's not that old a system.

00:22:12.910 --> 00:22:15.220
But it was all paperwork.

00:22:15.220 --> 00:22:17.260
And I don't know if
any of you have ever

00:22:17.260 --> 00:22:19.465
asked to see a grandparent's
or great grandparent's

00:22:19.465 --> 00:22:22.550
or an ancestor's passport
or those documents,

00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:23.500
if you have them.

00:22:23.500 --> 00:22:26.170
But they're intensely paper.

00:22:26.170 --> 00:22:28.240
In fact, if they're from
the late 19th century,

00:22:28.240 --> 00:22:29.690
there's no photographs.

00:22:29.690 --> 00:22:32.155
They started to have photographs
in the early 20th century.

00:22:35.730 --> 00:22:37.040
And so it's a big change.

00:22:37.040 --> 00:22:41.330
And the last 30 or 40 years
of digitisation of this

00:22:41.330 --> 00:22:45.020
has actually made it a
little harder, in some ways.

00:22:45.020 --> 00:22:46.190
I mean there's efficiencies.

00:22:46.190 --> 00:22:47.780
But it makes it harder.

00:22:47.780 --> 00:22:53.090
And then attestation is that
third party verifying it.

00:22:53.090 --> 00:22:54.770
And that's what Alin
was talking about.

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:59.030
If somebody can verify your
identity, they're basically--

00:22:59.030 --> 00:22:59.810
I make a claim.

00:22:59.810 --> 00:23:01.280
My name's Gary.

00:23:01.280 --> 00:23:03.980
I might give a credential,
my passport to show it.

00:23:03.980 --> 00:23:05.570
The picture looks like me.

00:23:05.570 --> 00:23:07.220
A human looks at it.

00:23:07.220 --> 00:23:08.900
Lines it up.

00:23:08.900 --> 00:23:10.220
Says all right.

00:23:10.220 --> 00:23:13.730
You can enter the
country of Germany

00:23:13.730 --> 00:23:17.670
or wherever I'm traveling.

