00:31:06.220 --> 00:31:08.940
Well, remember the New York
Times will have a public key.

00:31:08.940 --> 00:31:11.040
It will have a
corresponding secret key.

00:31:11.040 --> 00:31:13.732
So you visit their website.

00:31:13.732 --> 00:31:15.690
It turns out that when
you download the website

00:31:15.690 --> 00:31:17.670
from the New York Times
with that announcement

00:31:17.670 --> 00:31:19.800
about the snow storm,
that's actually signed

00:31:19.800 --> 00:31:24.990
with their secret key to verify
the website that you get.

00:31:24.990 --> 00:31:27.070
You verify it against
their public key.

00:31:27.070 --> 00:31:29.070
And you know that only
they know the secret key.

00:31:29.070 --> 00:31:31.695
So only they could have offered
that information and signed it.

00:31:31.695 --> 00:31:34.320
So then you know you're
dealing with the right website.

00:31:34.320 --> 00:31:36.583
