00:39:55.820 --> 00:39:57.930
Well, you sign with your secret
key that's on your credit card.

00:39:57.930 --> 00:39:59.210
So nobody knows your secret key.

00:39:59.210 --> 00:40:00.170
It's on your damn card.

00:40:00.170 --> 00:40:01.550
Never lose that card.

00:40:01.550 --> 00:40:02.720
And problem solved.

00:40:02.720 --> 00:40:05.215
They can steal as many
public keys as they want.

00:40:05.215 --> 00:40:05.840
Problem solved.

00:40:05.840 --> 00:40:07.070
Same thing with the SSN.

00:40:07.070 --> 00:40:08.650
Why would you share that--

00:40:08.650 --> 00:40:10.200
GARY GENSLER: I
disclosed to you.

00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:12.092
He became a maximalist, almost.

00:40:12.092 --> 00:40:14.300
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] I'm
talking about public crypto

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:15.970
here, not without consensus.

00:40:15.970 --> 00:40:18.150
Although, consensus can
be a very important part

00:40:18.150 --> 00:40:18.560
of all of this.

00:40:18.560 --> 00:40:19.120
GARY GENSLER: Almost.

00:40:19.120 --> 00:40:19.620
Almost.

00:40:19.620 --> 00:40:20.200
All right.

00:40:20.200 --> 00:40:21.740
So let me just hit.

00:40:21.740 --> 00:40:24.860
So in terms of the
big pain points--

00:40:24.860 --> 00:40:27.260
privacy and security, a
bunch of identity theft,

00:40:27.260 --> 00:40:29.900
forged credentials,
back to the passport

00:40:29.900 --> 00:40:31.610
or the driver's
license or the credit

00:40:31.610 --> 00:40:36.530
card, a forged credential,
whatever that is.

00:40:36.530 --> 00:40:40.640
And of course, just how do we
update our personal identity

00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:42.670
for any time we move?

00:40:42.670 --> 00:40:45.830
And this term PII
is three letters

00:40:45.830 --> 00:40:46.880
you'll learn in business.

00:40:46.880 --> 00:40:49.970
Because at some point in time
you'll be running a business

00:40:49.970 --> 00:40:53.420
and somebody will be coming
in, your chief of information

00:40:53.420 --> 00:40:55.610
officer, and say,
we've had a breach.

00:40:55.610 --> 00:40:58.190
And unfortunately we
broke some laws, too.

00:40:58.190 --> 00:41:02.330
Because in the US and
in other countries GDPR,

00:41:02.330 --> 00:41:03.740
you have to protect
certain data.

00:41:03.740 --> 00:41:05.990
And it's usually called PPI.

00:41:05.990 --> 00:41:09.890
It's usually the bucket of
data you need to protect.

00:41:09.890 --> 00:41:13.790
But every time you update your
personal information, how do

00:41:13.790 --> 00:41:18.185
you how do you keep it updated?

