It's not even on this.

00:44:10.420 --> 00:44:16.080
It wouldn't get to
the 50th page by size.

00:44:16.080 --> 00:44:18.540
But Wells Fargo had
other issues that was

00:44:18.540 --> 00:44:20.455
capturing the public attention.

00:44:20.455 --> 00:44:20.955
Kelly.

00:44:20.955 --> 00:44:22.320
AUDIENCE: Just taking
the Marriott one

00:44:22.320 --> 00:44:24.940
as an example, that's been the
most recent one in the news,

00:44:24.940 --> 00:44:25.890
I think.

00:44:25.890 --> 00:44:28.680
It's so costly to
these corporations.

00:44:28.680 --> 00:44:30.180
I think Marriott
even said that they

00:44:30.180 --> 00:44:34.785
would pay the fee to replace
passports for those affected.

00:44:37.410 --> 00:44:39.600
I mean, maybe it's a drop
in the bucket for them.

00:44:39.600 --> 00:44:45.300
But in terms of the
value in pain points,

00:44:45.300 --> 00:44:49.327
sort of like you were
talking about, it's a lot.

00:44:49.327 --> 00:44:50.410
GARY GENSLER: It is a lot.

00:44:50.410 --> 00:44:55.050
But one of the challenges that
blockchain technology solutions

00:44:55.050 --> 00:44:56.250
is adoption.

00:44:56.250 --> 00:45:02.800
How do you get Marriott to
contribute to a new system

00:45:02.800 --> 00:45:07.060
if you come up with a really
clever, creative, new system?

00:45:07.060 --> 00:45:10.390
Because there are so many
thousands of merchants

00:45:10.390 --> 00:45:15.080
that are trying to deal with
their cybersecurity risk.

00:45:15.080 --> 00:45:19.390
And Marriott, all of a
sudden, has all these costs.

00:45:19.390 --> 00:45:23.260
But how you get them involved in
your new blockchain technology

00:45:23.260 --> 00:45:26.800
solution, I think it's just
an adoption issue, which

00:45:26.800 --> 00:45:29.320
somebody might solve.

00:45:29.320 --> 00:45:31.390
Or as Ross says,
well, wait a minute.

00:45:31.390 --> 00:45:34.608
If the banks were to
just [INAUDIBLE] right?

00:45:34.608 --> 00:45:36.150
AUDIENCE: If they
want to cut the fee

00:45:36.150 --> 00:45:38.101
and let everybody
else-- then that's fine.

00:45:38.101 --> 00:45:42.237
But the merchants have
no bargaining power.

00:45:42.237 --> 00:45:43.320
GARY GENSLER: That's true.

00:45:43.320 --> 00:45:45.382
AUDIENCE: So they cut the fee.

00:45:45.382 --> 00:45:48.660
GARY GENSLER: So a couple
of state identity projects.

