Estonia has e-identity.

00:45:50.670 --> 00:45:55.110
They started in 2002, well
before blockchain technology.

00:45:55.110 --> 00:45:59.760
And it's run on a software
called X-Road software.

00:45:59.760 --> 00:46:03.390
And while some folks
might think of Estonia

00:46:03.390 --> 00:46:08.335
as a blockchain friendly
nation, does anybody

00:46:08.335 --> 00:46:10.710
want to take a guess whether
this software has blockchain

00:46:10.710 --> 00:46:13.720
technology?

00:46:13.720 --> 00:46:15.550
What's the consensus?

00:46:15.550 --> 00:46:16.060
No.

00:46:16.060 --> 00:46:18.640
It's not.

00:46:18.640 --> 00:46:21.090
That doesn't mean
it doesn't work.

00:46:21.090 --> 00:46:26.410
But they've sort of
wrapped themselves

00:46:26.410 --> 00:46:29.440
in this sort of spirit of
we're a blockchain nation.

00:46:29.440 --> 00:46:33.280
And they also have e-health
records and many other records

00:46:33.280 --> 00:46:35.380
that are going online.

00:46:35.380 --> 00:46:40.810
And it may be, at some
level, inspired by that.

00:46:40.810 --> 00:46:46.770
They have 1.3 million
people in Estonia.

00:46:46.770 --> 00:46:50.460
I think a bigger state
actor in the challenge--

00:46:50.460 --> 00:46:53.580
sorry, Brotish-- is Aadhaar.

00:46:53.580 --> 00:46:56.130
So there's a national
identification system.

00:46:56.130 --> 00:47:00.630
And it was promoted really for
inclusion, financial inclusion,

00:47:00.630 --> 00:47:05.670
and a way to get government
assistance and welfare

00:47:05.670 --> 00:47:10.260
to hundreds of millions of poor.

00:47:10.260 --> 00:47:12.270
India at the time that
it was rolled out,

00:47:12.270 --> 00:47:17.340
well over half of India did not
have a banking account at all.

00:47:17.340 --> 00:47:21.750
12 digit ID and biometrics,
being fingerprint and iris

00:47:21.750 --> 00:47:26.040
scan, I think they would deal
with the identical twin issue.

00:47:26.040 --> 00:47:34.260
I think, from my little example
that my twin brother Rob's

00:47:34.260 --> 00:47:37.710
finger didn't open my iPhone.

00:47:37.710 --> 00:47:39.250
But there's been
a lot of problems.

00:47:39.250 --> 00:47:41.610
And that's not a
blockchain project either.

00:47:41.610 --> 00:47:46.140
But my read of it is Aadhaar--

00:47:46.140 --> 00:47:48.000
and maybe Brotish
has some views--

00:47:48.000 --> 00:47:50.850
has done some very
positive things in India.

00:47:50.850 --> 00:47:55.110
But it's also come with
some very scary things.

00:47:55.110 --> 00:47:57.600
Brotish.

00:47:57.600 --> 00:48:00.210
AUDIENCE: It's a quick nugget
of information about Aadhaar.

00:48:00.210 --> 00:48:03.180
It was the fastest
system in the world

00:48:03.180 --> 00:48:05.700
to reach 1 billion users,
faster than Facebook

00:48:05.700 --> 00:48:08.890
or any other online platform.

00:48:08.890 --> 00:48:12.390
And [INAUDIBLE] optional, I mean
it was not a mandatory system

00:48:12.390 --> 00:48:13.560
for people to get it.

00:48:13.560 --> 00:48:14.660
It was optional system.

00:48:14.660 --> 00:48:17.200
But it was the fastest
one to reach 1 billion.

00:48:17.200 --> 00:48:19.170
GARY GENSLER: But it's optional.

00:48:19.170 --> 00:48:21.180
But you can't get your
government assistance

00:48:21.180 --> 00:48:22.830
any longer if you're
not in it, right?

00:48:22.830 --> 00:48:24.360
AUDIENCE: It's not like that.

00:48:24.360 --> 00:48:26.910
So actually, there has been
some government efforts

00:48:26.910 --> 00:48:28.410
to make it that way.

00:48:28.410 --> 00:48:30.900
But then the court actually
rejected those proposals.

00:48:30.900 --> 00:48:33.930
So they said that you cannot
make it mandatory to make

00:48:33.930 --> 00:48:36.360
people receive
benefits based on this.

00:48:36.360 --> 00:48:39.370
So whoever has that,
they might have some ease

00:48:39.370 --> 00:48:40.840
of obtaining those benefits.

00:48:40.840 --> 00:48:42.780
But it's not like without it,
you cannot get [INAUDIBLE]..

00:48:42.780 --> 00:48:44.822
GARY GENSLER: So Brotish
is saying it accurately.

00:48:44.822 --> 00:48:48.750
But the court only ruled that
this year during 2018 I think.

00:48:48.750 --> 00:48:51.383
And for a while, hundreds
of millions of people

00:48:51.383 --> 00:48:53.550
thought that's the only way
I can get my assistance.

00:48:53.550 --> 00:48:56.610
But the 12 digit ID
and the biometrics

00:48:56.610 --> 00:49:00.690
has produced a system where,
along with a payment system

00:49:00.690 --> 00:49:03.480
where you can do a QR
code right on your iPhone

00:49:03.480 --> 00:49:08.350
and get goods and services,
and it's pretty efficient.

